{#-
  Auth-SocialButtons — composable block of OAuth provider buttons (Ring 3 S3.1b).

  NOT a full-page pattern — does NOT compose `_auth-shell`. Drops INTO :
    - Auth-Login form body (below the password form)
    - Auth-Register form body (below the registration form)
    - Auth-SSO continuation page
    - Standalone "Sign in with…" page wrapped in `_auth-shell` at consumer level

  Composes :
    - Button (Ring 1) — via **compose-by-class** (`theme-button` styling
      envelope inherited via the class name). Does NOT `{% include %}`
      button.html.twig because Button's `iconLeading` param expects a
      Lucide curated-set icon name and brand marks (GitHub / Google /
      Apple / Microsoft) are NOT in the curated 30-set per OQ-52
      (sealed S3.1b opening).

  No Stimulus controller — pure server-rendered block. Consumer's OAuth
  flow lives on the server (each provider's `action` URL points at the
  consumer's OAuth start endpoint).

  Doctrine — consumer-driven raw SVG per provider :
    OQ-52 (sealed S3.1b opening) — `socialProviders[].icon` is a raw
    SVG string the consumer ships (Simple Icons / brand-provided assets).
    The kit renders it via Twig's `|raw` filter. Lucide upstream
    doesn't ship brand marks (semantic-glyphs-only philosophy) ; the
    kit's curated 30-set is NOT amended (ADR-0016 declined per S3.1c
    OQ-57b precedent extended).

  Security boundary :
    The consumer's SVG runs in-context — if the consumer ships
    untrusted user content as the SVG (anti-pattern : SVG can contain
    `<script>` / `onclick`), the consumer is responsible for
    sanitization. Same contract as Empty's `{% block illustration %}`
    slot.

  See `docs/specs/ring3/Auth-SocialButtons.md` for the full API + a11y +
  state documentation.
-#}

{%- set heading         = heading         | default('theme.auth.social-buttons.heading-or'|trans) -%}
{%- set socialProviders = socialProviders | default([]) -%}
{%- set orientation     = orientation     | default('vertical') -%}
{%- set buttonVariant   = buttonVariant   | default('secondary') -%}
{%- set size            = size            | default('md') -%}
{%- set htmlId          = htmlId          | default('theme-auth-social-buttons-' ~ random()) -%}
{%- set className       = className       | default('') -%}

{%- set _headingId = htmlId ~ '-heading' -%}

{%- set _classes = ['theme-auth-social-buttons'] -%}
{%- if className -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

<div class="{{ _classes | join(' ') }}" data-orientation="{{ orientation }}" id="{{ htmlId }}">
  {%- if heading -%}
    <p class="theme-auth-social-buttons__heading" id="{{ _headingId }}">{{ heading }}</p>
  {%- endif -%}

  <div
    class="theme-auth-social-buttons__list"
    {%- if heading %} aria-labelledby="{{ _headingId }}"{% endif -%}
  >
    {%- for provider in socialProviders -%}
      {% include '@theme/components/button/button.html.twig' with {
        label: provider.label,
        variant: buttonVariant,
        size: size,
        href: provider.action,
        iconLeadingRaw: provider.icon,
        className: 'theme-auth-social-button',
        attrs: { 'data-social-provider': provider.name },
      } only %}
    {%- endfor -%}
  </div>
</div>
